HeadsetControl
------------------------------------------
A tool to control certain aspects of USB-connected headsets on Linux.
Currently, support is provided for adjusting sidetone, getting battery state,
controlling LEDs, and setting the inactive time. See below for which headset
supports which feature.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.5.0-0.438.g322c7150b25e
  libhidapi0-0.8.0-rc1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.41-3
  cmake-3.25.3-1
  cygport-0.36.6-1
  gcc-core-11.4.0-1
  libhidapi-devel-0.8.0-rc1-1
  ninja-1.11.1-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/Sapd/HeadsetControl

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/Sapd/HeadsetControl/archive/refs/tags/2.7.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack HeadsetControl-2.7.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./HeadsetControl-2.7.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/HeadsetControl-2.7.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/HeadsetControl-2.7.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(HeadsetControl)
  /usr/bin/headsetcontrol.exe
  /usr/lib/udev/rules.d/70-headsets.rules
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/HeadsetControl.README
  /usr/share/doc/HeadsetControl/README.md
  /usr/share/doc/HeadsetControl/license

